original: Lindell, Nils Gustaf Magnus, kyrkoherde, Rävemåla, f. 17/9/04 i Örsjö, Kalmar 1., av kyrkoh. Axel L. o. Herta Engström. G. 32 m. skolköks-lär :an Carin Wångdahl. Barn: Monika f. 33, Kerstin 36, Ingegerd 40, Barbro 43. — Stud:ex. i Kalmar 23, fil. ämb :ex. i Lund 26, teol. kand. samt prakt. teol. prov 28, prästv. f. Växjö stift 29. Tjg. som v. pastor i Vickleby, past :adj. o. v. pastor i Vax-ho’lm, pred. v. Sthlms - läns sjukhem i Vaxholm, kommin. i örsjö, kyrkoh. i Älmeboda sed. 39. Ombud f. Sv. kyrkans miss :styr. i Konga kontr. E. o. ämneslär. v. Vaxholms komm. mel-lansk. o. samrealsk, 29-32, insp. f. Emmaboda samrealsk. sed. 46.
translated:
Lindell, Nils Gustaf Magnus, clergyman, Rävemåla, born 17/9/04 in Örsjö, Kalmar County, the son of Minister Axel L. and Herta Engström. Married in 1932 to school teacher Carin Wångdahl. Children: Monika (born 1933), Kerstin (born 1936), Ingegerd (born 1940), Barbro (born 1943). 

Education: Secondary school examination in Kalmar in 1923, Bachelor of Arts examination in Lund in 1926, Bachelor of Theology and practical theological examination in 1928, ordained as a priest for the Diocese of Växjö in 1929. 

Positions: Vicar in Vickleby, assistant pastor and vicar in Vaxholm, preacher at Stockholm County Hospital in Vaxholm, curate in Örsjö, and parish priest in Älmeboda since 1939. Delegate for the Swedish Church Missionary Board in Konga district. Temporary and subject teacher at Vaxholms municipal middle and secondary school from 1929 to 1932, inspector of Emmaboda secondary school since 1946.
